      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LIFE'S A JOKE (2) turned in a modest effort most recently when fifth at Murray Bridge over 300m behind Agent Twenty One (17.35) in a Grade 6. Speedy beginner who should be prominent early on from an inside box. Can discover winning form. SOKAI (7) is an honest type in the frame at four of 11 starts including five wins, the latest scoring (19.62) over 350m at Murray Bridge Straight. Goes very well at the trip finding the frame in each of five starts. Will go close here with a clear run. ELLA'S DESTINY (4) showed good early burn and was there until turning but swamped late to finish 6th at Murray Bridge in Grade 6 company. Has a good record here at this journey. Some good form is emerging from her last run. Has ability and is one of the better chances. SMOOTH PARADISE (1) should be thereabouts despite an unplaced run here most recently.",
